title: Linear Algebra, Multivariable Calculus, and Modern Applications
description: Multivariable calculus, linear algebra, and differential equations with applications.

title: Introduction to Bioengineering
description: Overview of bioengineering disciplines including biomechanics, tissue engineering, and medical devices.

title: Systems Biology
description: Quantitative modeling of biological systems. Gene networks, signaling pathways, and metabolic networks.

title: Bioengineering Fundamentals
description: Transport phenomena, thermodynamics, and kinetics in biological systems.

title: Bioengineering Laboratory
description: Laboratory techniques in bioengineering. Experimental design, data analysis, technical writing. Lab required.

title: Introduction to Biomechanics
description: Mechanics of cells, tissues, and organs. Stress-strain relationships and mechanical testing.

title: Tissue Engineering
description: Cell-biomaterial interactions, scaffold design, and regenerative medicine applications.

title: Biological and Medical Imaging
description: X-ray, CT, MRI, ultrasound, and optical imaging modalities. Image processing and reconstruction.

title: Chemical Principles I
description: Atomic structure, bonding, thermodynamics, and kinetics.

title: Chemical Principles II
description: Chemical equilibria, acids and bases, electrochemistry. Includes laboratory.

title: Organic Chemistry
description: Structure, bonding, and reactivity of organic molecules. Includes laboratory.

title: Mathematical Foundations of Computing
description: Discrete math, proof techniques, logic, and computational theory.

title: Programming Abstractions
description: Abstraction, recursion, data structures, and algorithms in C++.

title: Computer Organization and Systems
description: Computer architecture, memory hierarchy, and system-level programming in C.

title: Introduction to Probability for Computer Scientists
description: Probability theory, random variables, distributions, and statistical inference.

title: Principles of Computer Systems
description: Operating systems, concurrency, synchronization, networking, and distributed systems.

title: Design and Analysis of Algorithms
description: Algorithm design paradigms, complexity analysis, NP-completeness, and approximation algorithms.

title: Artificial Intelligence: Principles and Techniques
description: Search, constraint satisfaction, Markov decision processes, and machine learning.

title: Machine Learning
description: Supervised and unsupervised learning, deep learning, neural networks, and reinforcement learning.

title: Software Design Studio
description: Software engineering principles, design patterns, testing, and project management.

title: Independent Research
description: Supervised independent research project with faculty advisor.
